<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="372" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2126/56.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">British Ambassador</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-23"><hi rend="italic">January 23,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 223.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to inform you,
                            with further reference to your note No. 16 of the 20th instant in
                            connection with the revolutionary outbreak on the island of Haiti, that
                            the Secretary of the Navy informs the department, in response to its
                            request of the 21st instant, that the commanding officer of the U. S. S.
                                <hi rend="italic">Eagle</hi> has been directed by cable to afford
                            protection to British subjects and property pending the arrival at the
                            island of H. M. S. <hi rend="italic">Indefatigable</hi>.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>